## v0.81.0 (2025-06-29)

Source: https://github.com/templui/templui/releases/tag/v0.81.0

# templUI v0.81.0 – Triggers. Tags. Turbo. ⚡

## 🚀 What's New

* **🆕 TagsInput** (thx @derkan): Add/remove tags with `[]string` binding, `readonly`, `disabled`, and duplicate prevention
* **🔗 Decoupled Triggers:** Modal, Drawer, Popover now support `data-*-trigger` from *any* element
  → Use buttons, links, dropdown items, or multiple triggers per target – no more nesting needed
  → Better JS integration & Tailwind-friendly styling via `data-open`
* **📘 API Docs:** All components now have full API reference in the docs
* **💥 Breaking:** JS `initAllComponents` → now just `init()`
* **⚡ Smarter Swaps:** Components mark themselves with `initialized=true` → only new elements are re-inited after HTMX/Datastar swaps
* **🧹 Docs Cleanup:**

  * Better HTMX/Datastar usage
  * Removed CSP-related code
  * `card.Media` removed, examples use `aspect-ratio`
  * Typo fix (thx @brtholomy)

---

## 📦 Upgrade

```bash
go install github.com/axzilla/templui/cmd/templui@v0.81.0
```

👉 [Integration Guide](https://templui.io/docs/how-to-use#framework-integration)

---

templUI keeps getting leaner, faster, and more flexible. No lock-ins. No fluff. Just clean UI.

## v0.80.2 (2025-06-23)

Source: https://github.com/templui/templui/releases/tag/v0.80.2

# templUI v0.80.2 - Framework Agnostic Revolution 🚀

🛠️ Patch Note

This is a version bump release to sync the internal version with the actual tag.
No changes to the codebase – just fixing version mismatch from v0.80.0/v0.80.1.
If you're using go install, make sure to use v0.80.2.

> 🔥 **BREAKING CHANGES**: templUI is now completely framework-agnostic! Works seamlessly with HTMX, Datastar, or any hypermedia framework.

---

## 🎯 **Major Architectural Changes**

- **feat!:** Complete framework decoupling - templUI components now expose clean `window.templUI.*` APIs instead of hardcoded HTMX event listeners
- **feat!:** Remove HTMX-specific props from components (HxGet, HxPost, etc.) - use `templ.Attributes` instead for maximum flexibility
- **feat:** Add comprehensive framework integration documentation with examples for HTMX, Datastar, and manual initialization
- **feat(landing):** Add Gopher mascot image and enhance features section with detailed framework-agnostic benefits

---

## 📚 **Documentation Overhaul**

- **feat:** Enhance 'How To Use' documentation with structured sections and detailed integration guides
- **feat:** Add performance notes explaining HTMX vs Datastar trade-offs (targeted vs global re-initialization)
- **feat:** Add submenus to documentation navigation for better discoverability
- **fix:** Fix form component docs: Fixed select box href typo _(thanks @jaingounchained)_

---

## 🛠️ **Development Improvements**

- **chore:** Improve ESLint configuration for JavaScript files for better development experience
- **refactor:** Clean component APIs - all components now follow consistent `initAllComponents(root)` pattern

---

## ⚠️ **Breaking Changes & Migration**

### Before (v0.75.x):

```templ
@button.Button(button.Props{
    HxGet: "/api/endpoint",
    HxTrigger: "click",
}) { Click me }
```

### After (v0.76.0):

```templ
@button.Button(button.Props{
    Attributes: templ.Attributes{
        "hx-get": "/api/endpoint",
        "hx-trigger": "click",
    },
}) { Click me }
```

### Framework Integration Required:

#### HTMX Users:

```html
<script>
  // Re-initialize templUI components after HTMX swaps
  document.body.addEventListener("htmx:afterSwap", (e) => {
    if (window.templUI) {
      Object.values(window.templUI).forEach((comp) => {
        comp.initAllComponents?.(e.detail.elt);
      });
    }
  });

  // Re-initialize components after out-of-band swaps
  document.body.addEventListener("htmx:oobAfterSwap", (e) => {
    if (window.templUI) {
      Object.values(window.templUI).forEach((comp) => {
        comp.initAllComponents?.(e.detail.target);
      });
    }
  });

  // Optional: Cleanup before swap (for components with event listeners)
  document.body.addEventListener("htmx:beforeSwap", (e) => {
    if (window.templUI) {
      Object.values(window.templUI).forEach((comp) => {
        comp.cleanup?.(e.detail.target);
      });
    }
  });
</script>
```

#### Datastar Users:

```html
<script>
  // Re-initialize templUI components after Datastar fragment merges
  document.addEventListener("datastar-merge-fragments", (e) => {
    if (window.templUI) {
      Object.values(window.templUI).forEach((comp) => {
        comp.initAllComponents?.(document);
      });
    }
  });

  // Cleanup components when fragments are removed
  document.addEventListener("datastar-remove-fragments", (e) => {
    if (window.templUI) {
      Object.values(window.templUI).forEach((comp) => {
        comp.cleanup?.(document);
      });
    }
  });
</script>
```

---

## ✨ **Benefits of This Change**

- 🎯 **Framework Agnostic**: Works with HTMX, Datastar, Alpine.js, or any framework
- 🔮 **Future Proof**: Ready for whatever hypermedia framework comes next
- 🧹 **Cleaner APIs**: Consistent component interfaces across the board
- 📈 **Better Performance**: Targeted re-initialization where supported (HTMX)
- 🧪 **Easier Testing**: No framework dependencies in component code
- 🚀 **Broader Adoption**: Not tied to specific ecosystems

---

